("event_05_normal_1", "A country farmer stands before you on the road with a weeping girl behind him. He points his finger accusingly at one of your soldiers, saying that he raped his daughter and must be punished.^The soldier responds to the accusations, saying that he had just taken his daughter because the farmer attacked him while he tried to confiscate goods for the army."),
("event_05_normal_2", "A peasant stands before you on the road. He points his finger accusingly at one of your soldiers and says that he has stolen his ox.^The soldier responds to the accusations, saying that he had just confiscated the ox as law allows it."),
("event_05_normal_3", "A gardener stands before you on the road and says that one of your soldiers has stolen fruits and vegetables from his garden.^The soldier responds to the accusations, saying that he had just confiscated the fruits as law allows it."),
("event_05_normal_end", "end"),

("event_05_normal_1_1", "A soldier returns from his mission to fill the water reserves wounded and without any water. He says that a country farmer attacked him and prevented him from completing the mission. The soldier is known to be a liar and heavy drinker."),
("event_05_normal_1_2", "One of your soldiers accuses a local peasant of having offended and attacked him with a wooden stick. The soldier is known to be a trustworthy man."),
("event_05_normal_1_3", "An officer you sent to buy some supplies of daily need has accused a local gardener of having offended him. The officer said to the gardener he should go out of his way due to the peasant standing in his way. But instead of making room, the gardener threw stones at the officer and attacked him with a wooden stick."),
("event_05_normal_1_end", "end"),

("break_treaty_declare_war", "As {s63} feels frustrated by {s64} inactivity towards the matter, {s63} decides to use the opportunity to break the treaty with {s62} and declare war!"),
("provokations_between_allies", "{s63} asks {s64}, leader of the {s62}, to punish the troublemakers. But {s64} ignores {s63} pleas. This leads to future tensions between them."),
("provokations_between_allies_help", "{s63} asks {s64}, leader of the {s62}, to punish the troublemakers. On orders of {s64} the matter is investigated and resolved in favor of the {s61}."),

("lord_intro_lybian_feast_1", "Welcome {playername}. What a wonderful party! Back in Rome, such gatherings are far more... formal in my opinion. Here, there's a certain freedom, a looseness to the air. It's refreshing. I dare say, some of these Alexandrians live a little too freely, but perhaps that's part of the charm... Let's toast on the charm of Alexandria!"),
("lord_intro_lybian_feast_2", "Welcome to The Lybian's grand feast, {playername}! Alexandria never disappoints, and neither does our esteemed host. Have you seen the size of his trade network? No wonder the man holds such influence. Though, I must say, it's the wine that has my attention tonight - Greek, of course, only the finest."),
("lord_intro_lybian_feast_3", "Now, where did I leave my cup? Care to join me for another drink?"),

("wlod_4_temple_1", "You and Mancinellus enter the shrine of Artimpasa, and are welcomed by several androgynous Enarei, who seemed to be charmed by the two of you."
  +" You enjoy your time, that is until a Scythian chieftain enters the tent, hoping to receive a blessing by the Enarei, only to find you and Mancinellus despoiling them."
  +" You are chased out of the shrine, and together with your friend run back to your allies, since the two of you were shirtless, Wlodowiecus put two and two together and punches the both of you, then he launches himself at Mancinellus,"
  +" almost choking him to death but is stopped by you and a few others. You then quickly pack up before leading the caravan out of immediate danger."
  +" However, the Scythian chieftain quickly gathered a host of warriors, who began to pursue you for a couple of days, until you ran across an Alannic horde."
  +" Your guide quickly tells you that this tribe is not known to him, and soon arrows start to fly in your direction. It appears you are trapped between two armies."
  +" The good thing is, both the Scythians and the Alans despise each other!"
),
("wlod_4_temple_2",  "Mancinellus enters the shrine of Artimpasa, despite your warnings. The despoiling of the Enarei made the Scythians furious."
  +" Though, your own personal refusal to participate earned you some respect among the Scythians, despite being disobeyed by whom they define as your subordinate."
  +" They demand Wlodowiecus and the caravan to leave the temple immediately and never come back again. Wlodowiecus gathers the group and heads east, giving a very grim look of disapproval"
  +" at Mancinellus who seems to not notice that his disrespectful behavior again brought you trouble and screwed relations with locals."
  +" In a fit of rage, Wlodowiecus launches himself as Mancinellus, almost choking him to death but is pulled off him by you and some others."
  +" In your mind you wonder whether every time you enter some settlement, Mancinellus should be put under house arrest, watched by the Old Mercenary and Hadrianus to prevent him from following"
  +" his unhealthy urges and stupidity. Your internal thought debate is suddenly disturbed, as you see Alanic scouts shouting, warning about an Alan host which is about to attack you."
),
("wlod_4_temple_3", "You and Mancinellus enter the shrine of Artimpasa, and are welcomed by several androgynous Enarei, who seemed to be charmed by the two of you."
  +" You look for the priestess and enjoy your time with her, while Mancinellus is enjoying the Enarei nearby."
  +" Suddenly, a Scythian chieftain enters the tent, hoping to receive a blessing from the Enarei, only to find you and Mancinellus despoiling them."
  +" You are chased out of the shrine, and together with your friend run back to your allies, since the two of you were shirtless, Wlodowiecus put two and two together and punches the both of you,"
  +" launching himself at Mancinellus and almost chokes him to death but is stopped by you and a few others."
  +" You then quickly pack up before leading the caravan out of immediate danger. However, the Scythian chieftain quickly gathered a host of warriors,"
  +" who began to pursue you for a couple of days, until you ran across an Alannic horde. Your guide quickly tells you that this tribe is not known to him,"
  +" and soon arrows start to fly in your direction. It appears you are trapped between two armies. The good thing is, both the Scythians and the Alans despise each other!"
),
("fortress_jilu_looted", "The fortress is thoroughly looted and razed to the ground, though only a few valuables are discovered. The remaining guards are captured and imprisoned, left behind in the dungeons where Han reinforcements will undoubtedly find them. Later, a Xiongnu scout reports that a host of cavalry is approaching. You swiftly order a retreat."),
("fortress_jilu_retreat", "You immediately order a retreat to a nearby hill, where you set up camp to tend to wounds and rest. However, a Xiongnu scout soon reports that a host of Han cavalry is approaching."),

("event_grain_emperor", "As Princeps, you must decide: will you allocate emergency resources to secure alternative supplies, or let the populace fend for themselves and face potential unrest?"),
("event_grain_ai_help", "Caesar has acted decisively, ordering emergency measures to secure new grain supplies for the city. The people of Rome are relieved, though the treasury feels the strain."),
("event_grain_ai_ignore", "Despite the dire news of grain ships lost at sea, Caesar has chosen not to intervene. The markets grow barren, and murmurs of discontent rise among the Roman populace."),

("event_male_penetrating", "In the dim haze of the lupanar, shadows intertwine as laughter echoes faintly through the walls. A fleeting connection forms, a reminder of the many roles a man may play in the theater of life."),
("event_male_penetrated", "Behind closed curtains of the lupanar, the night becomes a lesson in surrender, where strength is redefined and trust momentarily exchanged."),
("event_male_blowjob", "Words dissolve into soft murmurs as the warmth of the moment carries away the weight of the world, leaving only fleeting sensations and stolen breaths."),
("event_female_classic", "The soft glow of a flickering lamp illuminates her impressive curves. A shared rhythm dances in the air, whispering of timeless exchanges and mutual solace."),
("event_female_butt", "In the small alcove of the lupanar, the fullness of the moment takes shape, both playful and indulgent, a celebration of round forms and passion."),
("event_female_blowjob", "The warm air thickens with hints of spice and desire, where words give way to knowing glances and quiet offerings beneath the golden lamplight."),

("event_caravan_sciri", "The caravan assembles at dawn, its wagons creaking under the weight of goods and hopes. The journey leads far to the North, toward the lands of the Sciri tribe, where the forests of the Balts whisper of ancient secrets.^^After a long journey through dense forests and cold winds, the caravan arrives at the Sciri settlement. Wooden halls rise amidst the trees, and the air carries the scent of pine and distant fires."),
("event_caravan_sagala", "Dust rises as the caravan begins its trek, the scent of spices and exotic wares mingling in the air. Ahead lies Sagala, an Indian town where golden temples and bustling markets promise treasures and stories untold.^^The caravan crests a hill, revealing Sagala in all its splendor. The town hums with life, its markets brimming with spices, silks, and the vibrant colors of India. Temples stand tall, their golden spires gleaming under the sun."),
("event_caravan_djenne", "Under the scorching African sun, the caravan ventures southward, crossing endless sands and verdant oases. Its destination is Djenne Djanno, a town of huts and timeless wisdom, nestled by the river's life-giving embrace.^^The caravan finally halts as Djenne Djanno comes into view. Mudbrick buildings glow in the afternoon light, and the nearby river glistens like a ribbon of silver. Traders and locals mingle, their voices rising in a harmonious hum."),
("event_caravan_karsahr", "The caravan snakes through rugged terrain, its path weaving between mountains and plains. Ahead lies Karsahr, at the far edge of the Ferghana Valley, where merchants and wanderers meet at the crossroads of the world.^^At last, the caravan reaches Karsahr, a bustling hub at the western edge of the Ferghana Valley. The aroma of exotic goods fills the air, and the sound of haggling merchants echoes through the streets. This is a place where cultures and stories converge."),

("priest_sacrifice_begin", "priest_sacrifice_begin"),
("priest_sacrifice_baduhenna", "Baduhenna, goddess of battle and defense, accept this sacrifice as a tribute to your might. Shield us from harm, guide our blades, and grant us victory against our enemies. May your protection be unwavering and your wrath devastating to those who oppose us."),
("priest_sacrifice_mars", "Mars, god of war and strength, to you we offer this sacrifice. Grant us courage in battle, unwavering discipline, and triumph over our foes. May your fiery spirit dwell within us, as we fight with honor in your name."),
("priest_sacrifice_dunraz", "Dunraz, mighty deity of the storm and sky, hear our call. Accept this sacrifice, and bless us with your power. May your winds guide us, your thunder inspire us, and your rain sustain our land."),
("priest_sacrifice_frijo", "Frijo, goddess of love and fertility, we honor you with this offering. May your blessings bring harmony to our homes, abundance to our fields, and joy to our hearts. Shine your grace upon us."),
("priest_sacrifice_vest", "Vesta, sacred keeper of the hearth, accept this sacrifice. Let your eternal flame bring warmth and unity to our homes and our people. May your protection and purity guide us always."),
("priest_sacrifice_saturn", "Saturn, ancient lord of time and harvest, to you we dedicate this offering. Bless us with your wisdom and ensure the fruits of our labor are plentiful. May your guidance lead us to prosperity."),
("priest_sacrifice_aphrodite", "Aphrodite, goddess of love and beauty, we humbly offer this sacrifice. Bestow your charm upon our lives, bring passion and unity to our bonds, and let your grace enrich our world."),
("priest_sacrifice_jupiter", "Jupiter, king of gods and ruler of the heavens, we offer this sacrifice in your honor. Bless us with your wisdom, protect us with your might, and guide our people with your justice."),
("priest_sacrifice_castor_pollux", "Castor and Pollux, divine twins of protection and victory, accept our offering. Watch over us, guide us in battle, and bless our endeavors with your celestial favor."),
("priest_sacrifice_christus", "Christus, Lord of compassion and salvation, we offer this sacrifice in reverence. Guide us in your light, grant us forgiveness, and inspire us to walk in your righteous path."),
("priest_sacrifice_yhwe", "YHWH, almighty and eternal, to you we dedicate this sacrifice. Bless your people with strength and wisdom, guide us in your commandments, and let your will be our shield."),
("priest_sacrifice_alcis", "Alcis, twin deities of harmony and strength, accept our offering. Unite us under your protection, and grant us balance and fortitude in all we do."),
("priest_sacrifice_mithras", "Mithras, bringer of light and protector of oaths, we honor you with this sacrifice. Guide us through darkness, uphold our promises, and grant us strength to overcome adversity."),
("priest_sacrifice_andraste", "Andraste, goddess of victory and vengeance, we dedicate this offering to you. Empower us in battle, crush our enemies, and let your fierce spirit guide us to triumph."),
("priest_sacrifice_maponos", "In the name of the good strength of the underworld gods, I invoke Maponos of Arverion. Pursue those with the magic of the infernals!"),
("priest_sacrifice_gebeleizis", "Gebeleizis, lord of storms and lightning, we offer this sacrifice to honor your power. Strike down our enemies, cleanse our lands, and protect us with your might."),
("priest_sacrifice_zalmoxis", "Zalmoxis, god of immortality and wisdom, we humbly offer this tribute. Grant us your knowledge, shield us from harm, and guide us on the path to eternity."),
("priest_sacrifice_goitosuros", "Goitosuros, healer and guardian of life, accept this offering. Bless us with health, protect our families, and grant us the strength to endure life's trials."),
("priest_sacrifice_artimpasa", "Artimpasa, goddess of fertility and war, we dedicate this sacrifice to your glory. Bless our fields and our warriors, and grant us prosperity in peace and victory in conflict."),
("priest_sacrifice_mihr", "Mihr, god of contracts and justice, accept this offering. Let your light shine on truth, uphold fairness in our dealings, and guide us to honor our bonds."),
("priest_sacrifice_armazi", "Armazi, mighty protector and ruler, to you we dedicate this sacrifice. Grant us your strength, shield us from harm, and bless our endeavors with your power."),
("priest_sacrifice_mazda", "Ahura Mazda, wise lord of creation, accept this offering as a sign of our devotion. Illuminate our path with truth, bring order to chaos, and guide us toward righteousness."),
("priest_sacrifice_allat", "Al-Lat, goddess of the earth and fertility, we offer this sacrifice in your name. Bless our lands with abundance, protect us from harm, and grant us your favor."),
("priest_sacrifice_ifri", "Ifri, guardian of the desert and protector of travelers, accept this sacrifice. Safeguard our journeys, bring prosperity to our ventures, and watch over our people."),
("priest_sacrifice_ammon", "Ammon, god of hidden strength and fertility, we honor you with this offering. Bless our endeavors, grant us your wisdom, and let your power sustain us."),
("priest_sacrifice_apedemak", "Apedemak, lion-headed warrior of the south, accept this offering. Bless us with your strength, protect our lands, and grant us victory over our foes."),

("sacrifice_description_begin", "sacrifice_description_begin"),
("sacrifice_description_baduhenna", "Baduhenna, goddess of battle and defense, demands a worthy sacrifice. I shall offer the blood of a mighty ram, its horns adorned with ribbons of red, symbolizing strength and protection. Alongside, I shall burn juniper branches to call for her shield to ward off our enemies."),
("sacrifice_description_mars", "For Mars, the god of war and valor, I will sacrifice a bull, its powerful form a tribute to his strength. Its blood shall anoint the altar, and weapons placed before him will symbolize the courage and discipline of those seeking his favor."),
("sacrifice_description_dunraz","Dunraz, the storm lord, demands a sacrifice fitting his tempestuous power. I will offer a black goat, its spirit symbolizing the restless skies. With it, I shall burn pine resin and cast barley into the flames, calling for his winds to favor us."),
("sacrifice_description_frijo","Frijo, goddess of love and fertility, shall receive a sacrifice of doves, their gentle spirits embodying harmony and affection. I will also offer sweet honey and fresh milk, poured over fragrant flowers to invite her grace upon our lives."),
("sacrifice_description_vest","Vesta, keeper of the sacred hearth, calls for a pure offering. I shall bring unblemished grain, fresh fruit, and olive oil to her flames. These gifts will honor her presence and ensure the warmth of her protection in our homes."),
("sacrifice_description_saturn","Saturn, lord of harvest and time, shall be honored with a sacrifice of a young lamb, its innocence representing the cycle of life. I shall also offer sheaves of wheat and ripe figs, thanking him for his bounty and seeking his guidance."),
("sacrifice_description_aphrodite","Aphrodite, goddess of beauty and love, will be pleased with offerings of rose petals, sweet wine, and fragrant myrrh. I shall also sacrifice a white dove, its purity symbolizing the devotion and harmony she inspires in mortal hearts."),
("sacrifice_description_jupiter","For Jupiter, king of gods and ruler of the heavens, I will sacrifice a majestic white bull, its strength and purity honoring his might. Laurel branches and incense shall be burned, their smoke rising to the skies as a plea for his favor."),
("sacrifice_description_castor_pollux","Castor and Pollux, divine twins, demand a dual offering. I shall sacrifice two lambs, representing their unity and celestial power. Alongside, I will burn frankincense and present olive branches to call for their guidance and protection."),
("sacrifice_description_christus","Christus does not demand blood sacrifices but offerings of faith and devotion. I will light a simple candle, symbolizing the light of his teachings, and offer bread and wine in reverence to his grace and sacrifice for humanity."),
("sacrifice_description_yhwe","YHWH requires no bloodshed, only pure devotion. I will burn the finest frankincense and myrrh, their smoke rising as a symbol of prayer. Alongside, I shall offer unleavened bread and dedicate the ceremony to his eternal glory."),
("sacrifice_description_alcis","The Alcis, guardians of harmony, shall receive two white stags, representing balance and unity. I will also present wreaths of oak leaves and pour mead upon the altar, seeking their blessing upon our endeavors."),
("sacrifice_description_mithras","Mithras, protector of oaths, calls for a sacrifice of a mighty bull. Its blood shall sanctify the ceremony, while sacred bread and water will be placed upon the altar, symbolizing purity and strength in his divine light."),
("sacrifice_description_andraste","Andraste, goddess of victory, shall be honored with the sacrifice of a warhorse, its strength and spirit a tribute to her power. I will also burn rowan wood and sprinkle its ashes, calling for her to guide us in battle."),
("sacrifice_description_maponos","Maponos, youthful god of vitality, shall receive a sacrifice of a young deer, its vigor representing renewal. I will also offer fresh spring water and blossoms, asking him to bless us with strength and endurance."),
("sacrifice_description_gebeleizis","For Gebeleizis, lord of storms, I shall sacrifice a black goat under an open sky. Lightning-shaped sigils will be carved into the earth, and I will burn cedarwood to honor his might and seek his protection."),
("sacrifice_description_zalmoxis","Zalmoxis, god of immortality, requires a solemn offering. I shall sacrifice a white ox, symbolizing purity, and burn sacred herbs as I pray for his guidance toward enlightenment and eternal wisdom."),
("sacrifice_description_goitosuros","Goitosuros, the healer, calls for a gentle offering. I will sacrifice a lamb, its innocence invoking his compassion. Medicinal herbs and clear water shall be offered, seeking his blessings for health and restoration."),
("sacrifice_description_artimpasa","Artimpasa, goddess of fertility and war, shall be honored with a sacrifice of a red mare, symbolizing life and power. I will also present barley and pomegranates, asking for her favor in both peace and conflict."),
("sacrifice_description_mihr","Mihr, god of justice and light, shall receive an offering of a white ram. I will burn frankincense and offer freshly baked bread, seeking his guidance to uphold truth and fairness in our deeds."),
("sacrifice_description_armazi","Armazi, the great protector, demands a sacrifice worthy of his power. I shall offer a bull and burn juniper branches, invoking his might to shield us from harm and grant strength to our people."),
("sacrifice_description_mazda","Ahura Mazda, the wise lord, requires a pure and reverent offering. I will present sacred fire, burn sandalwood, and offer milk and honey, symbolizing devotion and seeking his guidance toward righteousness."),
("sacrifice_description_allat","Al-Lat, goddess of the earth, shall receive offerings of wheat, dates, and milk. I will also sacrifice a white lamb, asking for her blessings of fertility, prosperity, and peace upon the land."),
("sacrifice_description_ifri","Ifri, guardian of travelers, shall be honored with a sacrifice of a goat, its strength symbolizing endurance. I will also burn desert sage, praying for her protection and guidance on the journeys ahead."),
("sacrifice_description_ammon","Ammon, god of fertility and hidden power, demands an offering of a strong ram. I will burn cedarwood and offer wine, seeking his wisdom and blessings upon our endeavors."),
("sacrifice_description_apedemak","Apedemak, lion-headed warrior, shall be honored with the sacrifice of a lion or a strong bull. I will also burn acacia wood and present golden ornaments, seeking his protection and strength in battle."),

("bad_omen_1", "As the sun sets, the campfire crackles ominously, casting long, flickering shadows. Suddenly, a raven lets out a series of harsh cries before flying directly overhead, disappearing into the blackened sky. The men murmur nervously—ravens are said to be harbingers of death. Whispers spread through the group, and unease settles heavily upon the camp."),
("bad_omen_2", "During the night, a strange wind sweeps through the camp, chilling everyone to the bone. It carries with it the faint sound of wailing, though no one can determine its source. The more superstitious among your party whisper of restless spirits, and the dread seems contagious. Sleep does not come easily that night."),
("bad_omen_3", "A traveling merchant crossing your path brings troubling news: a blood-red comet has appeared in the night sky, a sign of impending doom. Though you dismiss his words as nonsense, you notice many in your party exchanging fearful glances. Such tales have a way of taking root in men's minds."),
("bad_omen_4", "At dawn, you discover that a flock of vultures has taken roost near your camp. Their baleful eyes watch your every move, and their presence feels oppressive. The men begin to mutter darkly, and morale falters as their courage wavers under the birds' sinister gaze."),
("bad_omen_end", "bad_omen_end"),
("good_omen_1", "At sunrise, a beam of light breaks through the clouds, shining directly on your camp. The warm glow seems almost divine, and the men take it as a blessing from the heavens. Spirits rise as laughter returns to the camp, and the day begins with renewed vigor."),
("good_omen_2", "During the march, a white stag appears on a nearby hill, its proud figure standing against the horizon. Many take it as a sign of the gods' favor, a rare and auspicious sight. The men cheer and march onward with lifted hearts, believing success is surely ahead."),
("good_omen_3", "A strange, soothing breeze sweeps through the camp at dusk, carrying the sweet scent of blooming wildflowers. The oppressive weight of the journey seems to lift, and the men exchange hopeful smiles. Someone murmurs about the gods smiling upon the group, and morale surges."),
("good_omen_4", "In the dead of night, as the camp rests, the stars above shine with extraordinary clarity, their light forming shapes that some interpret as divine symbols. The party awakens refreshed, speaking excitedly of the vision. The stars, they believe, are guiding them to glory."),
("good_omen_end", "good_omen_end"),

